[{"id":"VR119586","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR119560.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The importance of the Church of Sainte-Foy as a pilgrimage site is reflected in the building's design through inclusion of which of the following features?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR119586_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The first figure presents a photograph of the exterior of a church with two towers.Â The second figure shows an interior view of the same stone church, consisting of a longitudinal space bordered by high stone piers with rounded arches and a second row of smaller rounded arches supported by columns above it. The longitudinal space leads to a shorter space with a higher ceiling than the rest of the interior, and ends in an area with semi-circular vaulting, which contains an altar with an arched row of columns behind it, and the rear wall of the building being visible behind the columns.\" height=\"396\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR119560.g07.png\" width=\"550\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"standalone_statement style:1\">The two images shown an exterior and interior view of the same building.</p>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A clerestory and compound piers</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A nave arcade and external buttresses</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">An ambulatory and radiating chapels</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A pair of towers and carved capitals</p>"],"answer":2}]